The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Smith Corner had a population of 594. The population density was {{convert|2,700.0|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Smith Corner was 149 (25.1%) [[White Americans|White]], 1 (0.2%) [[African Americans|African American]], 15 (2.5%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 0 (0.0%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 0 (0.0%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 357 (60.1%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 72 (12.1%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 517 persons (87.0%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Smith Corner CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0672338 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=June 4, 2025}}</ref>

The whole population lived in households. There were 148 households, out of which 65 (43.9%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 68 (45.9%) were married-couple households, 12 (8.1%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 40 (27.0%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 28 (18.9%) had a male householder with no partner present. 19 households (12.8%) were one person, and 5 (3.4%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 4.01.<ref name=DP1/> There were 121 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (81.8% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=Smith Corner CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0672338 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=June 4, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 203 people (34.2%) under the age of 18, 61 people (10.3%) aged 18 to 24, 155 people (26.1%) aged 25 to 44, 129 people (21.7%) aged 45 to 64, and 46 people (7.7%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 29.2{{nbsp}}years. For every 100 females, there were 80.5 males.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 160 housing units at an average density of {{convert|727.3|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 148 (92.5%) were occupied. Of these, 58 (39.2%) were owner-occupied, and 90 (60.8%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

